    {
      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 0,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nRegister a SECOND, genuinely independent reviewer of a DIFFERENT lineage from BOTH the Claude lead and the existing Gemini reviewer, behind the slice-1 registry interface, so the panel has real cross-vendor signal.\\n\\nEXACT FACTS: the lead is Claude (Claude-family); the supervisor is Codex/GPT-family; the working independent reviewer is Gemini. A Claude- or Gemini-family reviewer is CORRELATED with the lead/existing reviewer, so the second reviewer should be a distinct family. An agentic reviewer requires tool access + bounded read perms + durable transcript refs + receipt hashes (the same bar as Cursor); a JSON model reviewer is text_only.\\n\\nBLOCKING OPEN QUESTION \\u2014 resolve in PRD/grill with REAL evidence: which second-reviewer route actually returns real typed verdicts in the rigorous workflow? Probe (a) Cursor SDK with an alternate model (gpt-5.5/composer) + entitlement; (b) a GPT-family reviewer through the gateway (distinct from the Codex supervisor's role). Pick by evidence; capture failure context (never secrets).\\n\\nSCOPE (do):\\n1. Register a second working reviewer of a distinct provider_family; the panel now runs 2 real reviewers via the registry.\\n2. Record its lineage + assurance_grade truthfully (agentic only if it has tools + bounded read + transcript refs + hashes; otherwise text_only).\\n3. The conservative aggregator (slice 2) applies across both; a genuine outage of one still degrades honestly.\\n\\nNON-GOALS: do NOT add calibrated weighting; do NOT mislabel a text-only reviewer as agentic; do NOT change the conservative rules.\\n\\nACCEPTANCE:\\n- A rigorous run records TWO real independent verdicts from DIFFERENT families, each with lineage + assurance_grade.\\n- The conservative rules apply across both; a single-reviewer outage degrades honestly (no regression).\\n- Deterministic replay preserved (cassettes for both routes); full suite green; ledger + replay artifacts exported.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-second-reviewer-20260601/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"44ec20ca81f4b367497420abf2dd2d1b80dd85d5d90fa7a90060de9ba5f4b6f6\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-second-reviewer-20260601/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"c39a13fce9f539caec7781049086e06dc265083c565bb0d4472ab128b5394766\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-second-reviewer-20260601/source/issues.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"bf7f904165f43a3cdf073d3565f1df87ed303695910c2c572002f93e6492c3f6\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"tdd_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-second-reviewer-20260601/source/tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"351f63bb2db48167ec11e76d4178f72caeb291208839abf9d2c1fa275b97b3fe\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-second-reviewer-20260601/source/grill-findings-tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"3139fc5bcab309e27c5f2dd7a8e0f78c252067d8ab538f67e8936bbe82ab66cd\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"implementation_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-second-reviewer-20260601/source/implementation-plan.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"a16a7104a1b190668de3808bf28d5db0359cae407cbf0d7155f36facff4a0fd8\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"suggested_skills\": [\n    \"/lead\"\n  ],\n  \"task_id\": \"reviewer-panel-second-reviewer-20260601\"\n}\n",
